					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Actually, you know something? There was a raycasting demo for the NES not too terribly long ago. I think you could get something close to Mode 7 by using some simple raycasting.</div>
<br />My, my, my...
<br />
<br />Mode 7 is allow to do matrix transformation on a 2D surface to allow it to look like 3D, but it remains a flat surface you're walking/driving on.
<br />
<br />Raycasting comutes vectors and make it look more like 3D.
<br />
<br />The "ideal" would be a mode 7 ground and with a second layer of raycased graphics on the top of that, but the SNES isn't really capable to do that (in hardware, if you render everything in software it might become possible).</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
