				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I was just looking at impressive old games on a different forum and someone posted <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=btu-9rvbj2E&amp;t=8m20s" class="postlink">this video of Toy Story Racer for GBC.</a>
<br />
<br />I don't think it's actually rendering anything in 3D, rather it looks like they're playing a highly simplified and compressed full motion video in the background and drawing sprites on top of it.
<br />
<br />Would the NES have enough memory to do something like this, even one short track?  To me it's more impressive than Rad Racer's trickery or even SNES's Mode 7.</div>

